<h4 id="problem">Problem</h4>
<p>Given a complex number $z$, what’s the meaning of $e^z$?</p>
<ol>
  <li>Does it make sense ? It doesn’t make any sense.</li>
  <li>We can left this undefined, but just think about this
$
e(z)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{z^{n}}{n !}
$ in real number domain.</li>
</ol>

<ul>
  <li>Can we just replace z with complex number in the right part of this equation?</li>
  <li>of course, we can, but how about the right part of this equation.</li>
  <li>It’s reasonable, we just replace with complex number too.</li>
</ul>

